<p>An SME is defined by the Standard EU definition [Commission Regulation 2003/361/EC] as an enterprise that:</p>
<ul><li>has fewer than 250 employees</li><li>has a turnover of €50 million or less (or €43 million or less on their balance sheet)</li><li>is independent and autonomous, i.e. not part of a wider group of enterprises</li><li>has less than 25% of their capital held by public bodies</li><li>is established and operating in the Republic of Ireland</li></ul></p>
